lead_paragraph: Japanese golfer Haru Nomura held off world number one Lydia Ko down the stretch to land the Women's Australian Open in Adelaide on Sunday for her first LPGA Tour title.

headline.print_headline: Nomura Holds Off Ko to Land First LPGA Title
